[SN]TITLE[SN]
Motorist dies in crash between Leadburn and Howgate

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A motorist has died following a two-car crash in Midlothian.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The accident happened on the A6094 between Leadburn and Howgate at about 13:00 on Sunday.
Police said they were alerted by a member of the public. The emergency services, including fire crews from West Linton, Dalkeith and Penicuik, were sent to the scene.
Police Scotland confirmed one motorist had died and appealed for information on the crash.
A section of road between the Leadburn junction and Howgate was closed for a crash investigation and has since reopened.
